<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">anguage of a Chri&s;tian about <HI>Good,</HI> is that; P&s;al. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">.28. <HI>It is Good for me to Draw near unto God.</HI> The <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">in Concern</HI> lying upon the Heart of a Chri&s;tian <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> not, <HI>What he &s;hall Eat or Drink, or, wherewithal <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ll he be Cloathed?</HI> But, <HI>What &s;hall I do to be Saved?</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">he <HI>Plea&s;ures</HI> that a Chri&s;tian prefers, what are <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ey? Not, <HI>The plea&s;ures of &s;in;</HI> but, <HI>The plea&s;ant <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ayes of Wi&s;dom.</HI> The <HI>Riches</HI> that a Chri&s;tian pre|fers, what are they? Not, <HI>The Riches of Unrighteous <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ammon;</HI> but, <HI>To be Rich in Faith.</HI> And what are <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e <HI>Honours</HI> that a Chri&s;tian prefers? Not, <HI>Worldly <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">randeur,</HI> not, <HI>Humane Applau&s;e;</HI> but, <HI>The Prai&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">at comes from God.</HI> Where are the <HI>Affections</HI> of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Chri&s;tian? An&s;wer, Col. 3.2. <HI>Upon the Things that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">e Above.</HI> Hence, the Chri&s;tian, to prove, that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e does <HI>Chu&s;e</HI> the <HI>Good Portion,</HI> will rather <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o&s;e</HI> any thing el&s;e, than <HI>Lo&s;e</HI> that <HI>Portion.</HI> This <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">as the Temper of a <HI>Mo&s;es:</HI> [Heb. 11.25, 26.] <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nd it was the Temper of our <HI>Mary</HI> too.</P>
